    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">A turret in a tower defense game can only target enemies that are inside its range.<br><br>You are given the turret's coordinates (<var>x</var>, <var>y</var>), the turret's range <var>r</var>, and the number of enemies <var>n</var> followed by <var>n</var> lines with each of their x and y coordinates (<var>a</var>, <var>b</var>). An enemy is considered inside the turret's range if the Euclidean distance between the turret's coordinates and the enemy's coordinates is less than or equal to the turret's range.<br><br>You need to output the number of enemies that are within the turret's range. Good luck!<br><br><strong>Hint:</strong> Euclidian distance = <const>sqrt((x2-x1)^2+(y2-y1)^2)</const></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> Three space separated integers <var>x</var> and <var>y</var> representing the coordinates of the turret and <var>r</var> representing the turret range.<br><strong>Line 2:</strong> An integer <var>n</var> for the number of enemies.<br><strong>Next <var>n</var> lines:</strong> Two space separated integers <var>a</var> and <var>b</var> representing the <strong>x</strong> and <strong>y</strong> coordinates of an enemy.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> The number of enemies whose Euclidean distance is less than or equal to the turret's range <var>r</var>.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\"><const>-10000</const> &le; <var>x</var>, <var>y</var>, <var>a</var>, <var>b</var> &le; <const>10000</const><br><const>1</const> &le; <var>r</var> &le; <const>10000</const><br><const>1</const> &le; <var>n</var> &le; <const>50</const></div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">0 0 5\n2\n3 3\n5 -5</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-out\">1</pre>\n         </div>\n      </div>\n   </div>\n</div>"
